.TH "pcm_prepare" 9 "pcm_prepare" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcm_prepare \- implements prepare callback function for PCM middle layer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pcm_prepare
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
substream pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This callback is called when the PCM is "prepared". Format rate, sample rate,
etc., can be set here. This callback can be called many times at each setup.

Returns 0 on success or error code otherwise.
